<TITLE> Court issues order to arrest Rashiduzzaman Millat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 07 (bdnews24.com) A Dhaka court Sunday issued an arrest warrant for former MP of Jamalpur-1 Constituency Rashiduzzaman Millat for tax evasion in a case filed by the National Board of Revenue. According to case details, Millat is accused of hiding the true extent of his income and investments as well as evading tax worth Tk 4.51 crore. The former lawmaker is also accused of not declaring ownership of an apartment in Mohakhali, land in Uttara and a house in his home village in Kalikapur. Millat also stands accused hiding ownership of a Jeep and other cars in his tax returns for fiscal 1988-89 and 2005-2006. Judge Md Azizul Haque issued the arrest warrant. In a separate case filed Thursday, the Anticorruption Commission charged Millat, his wife Sabira Suraiya and their son Sayeed Bin Zaman with suppressing information on their wealth statement. The ACC filed the case with the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court. Millat has so far evaded capture. bdnews
